### English Title:
American Airstrikes in Yemen Result in High Casualties Among Houthi Workers

### English Text Summary:
On Friday, the Houthi-affiliated Al-Masirah channel reported that U.S. airstrikes on an oil port in western Yemen killed at least 38 people, marking one of the deadliest days since the U.S. intensified its military campaign against the Iran-backed group. The U.S. Central Command stated that the strikes aimed to cut off revenue sources for the Houthis, who have been exploiting their citizens. The airstrikes also injured 102 individuals, according to Houthi health officials. Despite claims of significant Houthi casualties, analysts suggest that key military and political leaders remain unharmed. The U.S. military operation has reportedly cost nearly a billion dollars over three weeks, with limited impact on the group's capabilities. Meanwhile, the Houthis continue to launch missiles at Israel and threaten U.S. naval vessels.

